deck_name: Prophesy of Horus: Black Flames Rise
deck_excerpt: “Evil as well as good, both operate to advance the Great Plan.” ― Muata Ashby, Egyptian Book of the Dead
deck_description: This deck was interesting to build for me, because I had heard of the Egyptian god cards many times, but i have never heard of the 'Horus' archetype before making this deck. However, after looking into the cards, they are very intersting to me due to the way they function. the 'Sons of Horus' cards can come back once as long as 'King's Sarcophagus' is in play. along with the aforementioned 'Son's of Horus', there are many available cards to support 'King's Sarcophagus'. In addition, the use of 'Orcustrated Babel' allows for many cards to use their abilities despite not even being on the field. Once again, as for the rest of my decks I have made, I used https://theresanaiforthat.com/@mmrgaming/yugioh-deck-builder for the base design of this deck, however, this time I have made considerable changes to the suggested cards the builder gave me. If you have any ideas to improve the deck, please let me know.
This is my deck, which I love really much.

Basic idea here is that Deception triggers the Mitsurugi effects.

Primite cards get you into Feral Imp and can be ritual fodder.

Ratios still TBD.

 

Some misc synergies:

  • Feral Imp + a lv4 -> Twins -> pop via N'tss to summon Feral Imp and search again
  • Lizardose can banish a Mitsurugi for a draw then the card can still be added back via Kusanagi
  • If you use the summon effect of Lode, it only restricts effects on field, so you can still get the Mitsurugi effects when they are tributed

deck_name: Shark post MAZE OF THE MASTER
deck_description:
We be eating good after March in TCG

We be eating bad cause dam Ryzeal uses tachyon too :(

Hydrojet shark + the 2 corresponding trap & spell is for testing, unsure how useful it really is yet.

Eclipse twin is also a flex spot (need testing), otherwise can just put C101 and rank up magic in MD which seventh can search for if needed.

9 real HT (ash, impulse, imperm) and 6 draws HT. 15 total.

Unsure of mischief in this deck atm. Side board is just mostly fillers.

Search for Vaalmonica, the Agathokakological Voice by using Rainbow Bridge of Salvation's graveyard effect. Send Rainbow Bridge to the graveyard by discarding it or send it from the deck to the graveyard with Foolish Burial Goods. If Crystal Beast Topaz Tiger is in your hand, then you can shuffle it back into the deck with Vaalmonica Scelta's effect.
